    {
      "id": "CVE-2026-23555",
      "publishedDate": "2026-03-23T06:57:07.653Z",
      "lastModifiedDate": "2026-03-23T07:32:28.482Z",
      "description": "Any guest issuing a Xenstore command accessing a node using the\n(illegal) node path \"/local/domain/\", will crash xenstored due to a\nclobbered error indicator in xenstored when verifying the node path.\n\nNote that the crash is forced via a failing assert() statement in\nxenstored. In case xenstored is being built with NDEBUG #defined,\nan unprivileged guest trying to access the node path \"/local/domain/\"\nwill result in it no longer being serviced by xenstored, other guests\n(including dom0) will still be serviced, but xenstored will use up\nall cpu time it can get.",
      "severity": "N/A",
      "references": [
        {
          "url": "https://xenbits.xenproject.org/xsa/advisory-481.html",
          "type": "reference"
        }
      ],
